$ Predefined preprocessor macros __FUNCTION__, __FILE__, __LINE__


Note, `__FUNCTION__` is not really a macro: the preprocessor has now concept of functions and thus doesn't not know in which function it is.

{ print_function.h

gh|about-cpp|/preprocessor/macros/predefined/__FUNCTION__FILE__LINE__/print_function.h||

}

{ funcs.c

gh|about-cpp|/preprocessor/macros/predefined/__FUNCTION__FILE__LINE__/funcs.c||

}
{ main.c

gh|about-cpp|/preprocessor/macros/predefined/__FUNCTION__FILE__LINE__/main.c||

}
{ funcs.h

gh|about-cpp|/preprocessor/macros/predefined/__FUNCTION__FILE__LINE__/funcs.h||

}
{ Makefile

gh|about-cpp|/preprocessor/macros/predefined/__FUNCTION__FILE__LINE__/Makefile||

}

